cyChop:
Just an afterthought: returning the paper after drawing the SVG would leave these options available.

To do it the hard way, here is a skeleton of something that worked on your gh-page:

``` css
#wrapper { height: 200px; width: 200px; }
#wrapper svg { height: 100%; width: 100%; }
```

``` javascript
$('#demo .diagram').append($('<div>', { id: 'wrapper'}).append($('#demo .diagram svg').remove()));
var svg = $('#wrapper svg');
// attr() breaks the case, and viewBox and preserveAspectRatio seem to be case-sensitive
svg.get(0).setAttribute('viewBox', '0 0 ' + svg.attr('width') + ' ' + svg.attr('height'));
svg.get(0).setAttribute('preserveAspectRatio', 'xMidYMid');
```

Still, less elegant than doing it natively.

Thanks for the great library otherwise!
